.TH RULERQUERY 1
.SH NAME
rulerquery \- query ruler for configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rulerquery
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Rulerquery
reads a ruler request from standard input and prints the response to standard output.
The request must be in the format of
.MR ruler 7 :
one attribute per line
.RB ( query= value ,
.BR client= value ,
.BR event= value ,
.BR id= value ).
All four attributes are required.
.PP
.I Rulerquery
connects to the
.MR ruler 4
service, opens
.BR ruler/query ,
writes the request, then reads and prints the response.
It is intended for testing rulerfiles and debugging; editors such as
.MR acme 1
query ruler directly when opening files.
.PP
Example:
.EX
	echo 'query=/tmp/foo.go
	client=acme
	event=open
	id=1' | rulerquery
.EE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.MR ruler 4 ,
.MR ruler 7
